00:00:19,626 --> 00:00:37,187
[SPEAKER_05]: present to present one absent the meetings called to order, there'll be a meeting of the Medford City Council subcommittee on ordinances and rules on Wednesday, March 8 2023 at 530pm in the Medford City Council chamber on the second floor of Medford City Hall and via zoom purpose of this meeting is to discuss the proposed waste hauler ordinance paper 22 dash 605.

5
00:00:39,089 --> 00:00:45,159
[SPEAKER_05]: The subcommittee has invited DPW Commissioner Tim McGivern and Alicia Hunt, Director of Planning, Development and Sustainability, to attend this meeting.

6
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:49,085
[SPEAKER_05]: For further information, aids and accommodations, contact the City Clerk at 781-393-2425.

7
00:00:49,105 --> 00:00:50,347
[SPEAKER_05]: Sincerely yours, Zach Baer, Subcommittee Chair.

8
00:00:55,103 --> 00:00:59,447
[SPEAKER_05]: Welcome everyone to our subcommittee on ordinances and rules meeting.

9
00:01:00,167 --> 00:01:10,977
[SPEAKER_05]: We are meeting to discuss a proposed updates to the city's, well, a proposed waste hauler ordinance, which would update several elements of the city's current solid waste ordinances.

10
00:01:11,857 --> 00:01:22,286
[SPEAKER_05]: This project is parallel to recent work by the Planning and Development Sustainability Office and the Solid Waste Task Force to create recommendations for an RFP for a new municipal waste hauler contract.

11
00:01:22,967 --> 00:01:28,954
[SPEAKER_05]: This is an opportunity to align our waste hauling ordinances with current best practices from the Massachusetts Department of Environmental Protection.

12
00:01:29,454 --> 00:01:32,998
[SPEAKER_05]: By adopting these, we can earn more points on the state's recycling dividends program.

13
00:01:33,679 --> 00:01:40,666
[SPEAKER_05]: As everyone knows, municipal waste hauling is a massive budget item, so maximizing grant funding is meaningful, especially around education efforts.

14
00:01:41,327 --> 00:01:58,982
[SPEAKER_05]: And the goal of this process in addition to the RFP process is to make sure that both within and outside of the municipal contract for waste removal, all solid waste haulers are providing a recycling service and to create clear updated requirements for waste haulers in alignment with our environmental goals and state and regional best practices.

15
00:02:02,022 --> 00:02:07,404
[SPEAKER_05]: And we had some discussions a couple of weeks ago around the solid waste RFP.

16
00:02:07,484 --> 00:02:13,727
[SPEAKER_05]: And I think you could find more details about that by watching the recording of that meeting or looking at the minutes of that meeting.

17
00:02:14,207 --> 00:02:24,792
[SPEAKER_05]: And I would also add that there was some discussion around how this waste tolerance ordinance fits into that larger process that we may not talk about tonight, but that you could find watching that recording or listening to those minutes.

18
00:02:25,932 --> 00:02:38,459
[SPEAKER_05]: Given that introduction, I will turn over to Councilor Collins, who's the lead sponsor of this, and then we can have a discussion with our DPW Commissioner and PDS Director about where we go from here.

