[SPEAKER_03]: Thank you, Alicia Hunt, Director of Planning, Development and Sustainability for the city.

39
00:05:13,684 --> 00:05:34,077
[SPEAKER_03]: We've been particularly interested in an ordinance like this for a long time because a lot of the bulk of this ordinance is about requiring companies to provide trash and recycling services for the same bundled rate as if they were to provide just trash or just recycling.

40
00:05:34,097 --> 00:05:35,158
[SPEAKER_03]: And over the last

41
00:05:36,045 --> 00:05:45,285
[SPEAKER_03]: In the last 10 years, it has come to my attention on many occasions when private residents who live in commercial buildings right multifamily, in particular,

42
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,941
[SPEAKER_03]: My building doesn't have recycling.

43
00:05:49,521 --> 00:05:54,044
[SPEAKER_03]: Is there a way that the city can make my building do recycling?

44
00:05:54,104 --> 00:05:56,005
[SPEAKER_03]: Like, why don't we have recycling?

45
00:05:56,745 --> 00:06:13,034
[SPEAKER_03]: And it's a difficult conundrum because the state law is actually that there are waste bans, which mean you cannot put items that should be recycled into trash in Massachusetts, but it's not enforced at the level of these local buildings.

46
00:06:13,535 --> 00:06:21,440
[SPEAKER_03]: It's enforced at a much higher level where they look at trash trucks and how much recycled content is coming out of them.

47
00:06:21,841 --> 00:06:26,804
[SPEAKER_03]: And there's very little enforcement at the state level because it's been underfunded, the enforcement of that.

48
00:06:29,025 --> 00:06:38,752
[SPEAKER_03]: So in theory, their building should be providing recycling services to them, but there's nobody who has the authority to make their building do that.

49
00:06:39,198 --> 00:06:43,040
[SPEAKER_03]: and their building isn't incentivized to do it in any way.

50
00:06:43,060 --> 00:06:59,727
[SPEAKER_03]: And one would hope that if the cost of trash and recycling together was the same as a cost of one or the other, then there would be no financial disincentive to providing recycling for these buildings and people would be able to do the right thing.

51
00:07:00,893 --> 00:07:04,875
[SPEAKER_03]: So it's good for our residents, we hear from them about it.

52
00:07:05,315 --> 00:07:19,681
[SPEAKER_03]: We hear from businesses who think they don't have recycling available to them, or they're not paying for recycling or they can't afford the extra, you know, so it would be good if they basically if it was there for them.

