55
00:07:42,660 --> 00:07:53,126
[SPEAKER_03]: And as part of that, we would require that preferred vendor to provide this bundled trash and recycling services for the city.

56
00:07:56,188 --> 00:08:05,754
[SPEAKER_03]: The benefit of creating a preferred hauler is that they would give fixed discounted, basically residents, anybody who's not on Medford's regular trash service.

57
00:08:05,914 --> 00:08:09,937
[SPEAKER_03]: So multifamily buildings, larger commercial entities could then,

58
00:08:10,799 --> 00:08:15,441
[SPEAKER_03]: get quote Medford's rates, Medford's contracted rate for waste services.

59
00:08:15,521 --> 00:08:18,202
[SPEAKER_03]: So they wouldn't have to go out and figure it all out themselves.

60
00:08:20,482 --> 00:08:22,843
[SPEAKER_03]: This ties hand in hand with that.

61
00:08:22,883 --> 00:08:36,628
[SPEAKER_03]: So we are trying to get that discounted rate for the city, but we don't want other businesses to then also be able to undercut our preferred hauler by saying, well, I'll just provide trash services for you at a lower rate.

